      "content": "you mentioned wind needs massive infrastructure investment, but doesn't that ignore the fact that gas has its own massive footprint with drilling and pipelines? and isn't it a bit of a stretch to call gas a \"transitional fuel\" when it's still a fossil fuel? feels like you're leaning towards wind being better just because it's labeled clean.",
